TerranVehicleAndShipArmorsLevel2.Name: Terran Vehicle and Ship Plating Level 2

CommandCenter.Description:
Primary structure. Used to receive gathered resources. Can use the Lift Off ability and can upgrade into an Orbital Command or a Planetary Fortress.

Enables:
- SCVs
CommandCenter.Name: Command Center

OrbitalCommand.Description: Primary structure. Used to train SCVs and receive gathered resources. Can use the Scanner Sweep ability. Can use the abilities Calldown: MULE and Calldown: Extra Supplies.
OrbitalCommand.Name: Orbital Command

OrbitalCommandFlying.Description: Primary structure. Must land to receive resources, produce units, or use abilities.
OrbitalCommandFlying.Name: Orbital Command

SCV.Description:
Basic worker unit. Can gather resources, build Terran structures, and repair.

Can attack ground units.
SCV.Name: SCV

Refinery.Description: Built over a Vespene Geyser to allow harvesting of vespene gas.
Refinery.Name: Refinery

SupplyDepot.Description:
Provides supply.
Supply allows you to create more units.
Supply Depots can be lowered to allow units to walk over them.
SupplyDepot.Name: Supply Depot

SupplyDepotLowered.Description:
Provides supply.
Supply allows you to create more units.
Supply Depots can be lowered to allow units to walk over them.
SupplyDepotLowered.Name: Supply Depot

Barracks.Description:
Infantry-production facility.

Enables:
- Marines
- Reapers
- Bunkers from SCVs
- Orbital Commands from Command Centers
Barracks.Name: Barracks

BarracksFlying.Description: Barracks must land to start unit production.
BarracksFlying.Name: Barracks

BarracksReactor.Description: Allows 2 units to be created simultaneously.
BarracksReactor.Name: Reactor

BarracksTechLab.Description: Enables additional units and research options. A Tech Lab can fit onto any production structure.
BarracksTechLab.Name: Tech Lab

Marine.Description:
General-purpose infantry.

Can attack ground and air units.
Marine.Name: Marine

Marauder.Description:
Heavy assault infantry.

Can attack ground units.
Marauder.Name: Marauder

Ghost.Description:
Sniper. Can use Steady Targeting, EMP Round, and be upgraded to use Cloak. Can call down Tactical Nukes built at the Ghost Academy.

Can attack ground and air units.
Ghost.Name: Ghost

Reaper.Description:
Raider. Can jump up and down cliffs. Regenerates life quickly while out of combat. Can use KD8 Charge.

Can attack ground units.
Reaper.Name: Reaper

EngineeringBay.Description:
Contains upgrades for Terran infantry and structures.

Enables:
- Missile Turrets from SCVs
- Sensor Towers from SCVs
- Planetary Fortresses from Command Centers
EngineeringBay.Name: Engineering Bay

Bunker.Description:
Defensive structure.
Infantry fights from inside.

Bonus: +1 range to units inside.
Bunker.Name: Bunker

MissileTurret.Description:
Anti-air defensive structure.

Can attack air units.
Detector
MissileTurret.Name: Missile Turret

SensorTower.Description: Reveals the locations of enemy units at long range. The Sensor Tower's detection area is visible to the enemy.
SensorTower.Name: Sensor Tower

GhostAcademy.Description:
Contains upgrades for Ghosts. Can build Nukes for Ghosts.

Enables:
- Ghosts at the Barracks
GhostAcademy.Name: Ghost Academy

Factory.Description:
Vehicle-production facility.

Enables:
- Hellions
- Widow Mines
- Cyclones
Factory.Name: Factory

FactoryFlying.Description: Factory must land to start unit production.
FactoryFlying.Name: Factory

FactoryReactor.Description: Allows 2 units to be created simultaneously.
FactoryReactor.Name: Reactor

FactoryTechLab.Description: Enables additional units and research options. A Tech Lab can fit onto any production structure.
FactoryTechLab.Name: Tech Lab

Hellion.Description:
Fast scout. Has a flame attack that damages all enemy units in its line of fire. Can transform into a close range combat unit.

Can attack ground units.
Hellion.Name: Hellion

HellionTank.Description:
Close range combat unit. Deals damage in a small frontal cone. Can transform into a fast scout unit.

Can attack ground units.
HellionTank.Name: Hellbat

SiegeTank.Description: Heavy tank. Can switch into Siege Mode to provide long-range artillery support.**Can attack ground units**
SiegeTank.Name: Siege Tank

SiegeTankSieged.Description:
Heavy tank. Can switch into Tank Mode to provide mobile tank support.

Can attack ground units.
SiegeTankSieged.Name: Siege Tank

WidowMine.Description:
Robotic mine. Launches missiles at nearby enemy units while burrowed. Attacks deal splash damage in a small area around the target. Widow Mine is revealed when Sentinel Missile is on cooldown.

Can attack ground and air units.
WidowMine.Name: Widow Mine

WidowMineBurrowed.Description:
Robotic mine. Launches missiles at nearby enemy units while burrowed. Attacks deal splash damage in a small area around the target. Widow Mine is revealed when Sentinel Missile is on cooldown.

Can attack ground and air units.
WidowMineBurrowed.Name: Widow Mine

Cyclone.Description:
Mobile assault vehicle. Can use Lock On to quickly fire while moving.

Can attack ground and air units.
Cyclone.Name: Cyclone

Thor.Description:
Heavy assault mech.

Can attack ground and air units.
Thor.Name: Thor

ThorAP.Description:
Heavy assault mech.

Can attack ground and air units.
ThorAP.Name: Thor

Armory.Description:
Contains weapon and armor upgrades for Factory and Starport units.

Enables:
- Hellbat at the Factory
- Thor at the Factory
Armory.Name: Armory

Starport.Description:
Air-unit production facility.

Enables:
- Vikings
- Medivacs
- Liberators
Starport.Name: Starport

StarportFlying.Description: Starport must land to start unit production.
StarportFlying.Name: Starport

StarportReactor.Description: Allows 2 units to be created simultaneously.
StarportReactor.Name: Reactor

StarportTechLab.Description: Enables additional units and research options. A Tech Lab can fit onto any production structure.
StarportTechLab.Name: Tech Lab

VikingFighter.Description:
Durable support flyer. Loaded with strong anti-capital air missiles. Can switch into Assault Mode to attack ground units.

Can attack air units.
VikingFighter.Name: Viking

VikingAssault.Description:
Durable support unit. Can switch into Fighter Mode to attack air units.

Can attack ground units.
VikingAssault.Name: Viking

Medivac.Description: Air transport. Heals nearby biological units. Can use Afterburners.
Medivac.Name: Medivac

Raven.Description:
Aerial support unit. Can use Auto-Turret, Interference Matrix, and Anti-Armor Missile.

Detector
Raven.Name: Raven

AutoTurret.Description:
Automated defensive turret. Times out after 14 seconds.

Can attack ground and air units.
AutoTurret.Name: Auto-Turret

Banshee.Description:
Tactical-strike aircraft. Can be upgraded to use cloak.

Can attack ground units.
Banshee.Name: Banshee

Battlecruiser.Description:
Powerful warship. Can use Yamato Cannon and Tactical Jump.

Can attack ground and air units.
Battlecruiser.Name: Battlecruiser

Liberator.Description:
Artillery fighter. Loaded with missiles that deal area damage to enemy air targets. Can switch into Defender Mode to provide siege support.

Can attack air units.
Liberator.Name: Liberator

FusionCore.Description:
Contains Medivac, Liberator, and Battlecruiser upgrades.

Enables:
- Battlecruisers at the Starport
FusionCore.Name: Fusion Core

MULE.Description: Prototype harvesting unit. Gathers minerals more quickly than regular SCVs. MULEs last 90 before their systems fail.
MULE.Name: MULE

PlanetaryFortress.Description:
Defensive stronghold.
Used to receive gathered resources. **Can attack ground units**
PlanetaryFortress.Name: Planetary Fortress

CommandCenterFlying.Description: Primary structure. Must land to receive resources, produce units, or use abilities.
CommandCenterFlying.Name: Command Center
